Bruce Cook, who owns Kaktus Point Charolais stud at Lake Charm, northwest of Victoria, has been warned by police that he may face charges .
He put up his 'realistic' hay bale structure on Good Friday just for 'a bit of fun'
The 59-year-old says many passersby have enjoyed his sculpture and even stopped to take photos .
Mr Cook says he will add fairy lights to the structure tonight and plans to add two more calves .